    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="620"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d620">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Pera</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 12, 1895</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Exequaturs often urged, not yet issued. Changes in the ministry have blocked
                    business at the Sublime Porte. Exequatur for Erzeroum promised, but it is
                    dangerous to travel. Harpoot refused because there is no other consul there and
                    we have not commerce.</p>
                <p>There has been great massacre at Malatia; four Jesuits killed. I fear that this
                    Government can not restore tranquillity even if it desired. Representative
                    Americans here desire me to telegraph the opinion that over 100,000 women and
                    children are destitute as a result of the massacres of last month, which still
                    continue. Great apprehension of danger still exists here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
